This year's Big Day of Play is on Saturday, August 16th from 12 p.m.-5 p.m. at Rainier Community Center and Playfields. Volunteer shifts are available from 9:30am to 7pm.

Big Day of Play is a celebration of our City’s diversity and it encourages neighbors, communities and families to have fun, build relationships and be active together.

Volunteers will choose from one of the following volunteer activities during their shift:

- Field Activities
- Greeter and Transportation Support
- Surveyors/Data Collection
- Water and Cooling Stations
- Water Slide and Inflatables Crowd Support

Service learning credit is available for students, up to 8 hours. You must be 14+ to volunteer. Groups of most sizes are welcome!
